    • caption

    • assignableValues

      protected SubjectFilterType.AssignableValues assignableValues
      Configuration of the user-rights editor

    • op

      protected String op
      Comparison operator, defaults to '='.

    • name

      protected String name
      Unique Name of this FilterType definition. Will be referenced in the SubjectFilter/@type attribute in a BindingSet and will be the name of the filter type, for example given in bcd_sec_user_settings in right_type, unless overwritten with @type.

    • type

      protected String type
      Overwrites the filter type to map to in [bcd_sec_user_settings].right_type, i.e. you can define different filters all mapped to same type to realize relations like having origin_country or destination_country permission set defined by 'country' acl.

    • isNullAllowsAccess

      protected Boolean isNullAllowsAccess
      Enables null-value evaluation on data to be filtered. i.e. when using boolean security flags like 'isRestricted' you can set it to null value and set this attribute to true to allow accessing the data.

    • mode

      protected String mode
      Defines on which operations this filter type is being enabled. (R)ead operations only, (W)rite operations only, or both (RW) which is the default.
